snippet.textDisplay: I have very CORSE very CURLY VERY DARK hair... and I bleached it on my own about a week ago now? It wasn’t Virgin, at least my ends because I had it dyed at the hair salon purple back in August, but I had a ton of growth and decided I would give doing it on my own a shot because I don’t like any of the hairstylists that live in my area. I did it with box dye. First I used the manic panic 30 volume developer box bleach, two of them, and I wish I would have ordered two more, but I didn’t. I got the same box bleach the girl had in this video from cvs as a last resort, and let me tell you THAT SHIT WAS FUCKING POWERFUL, like way way way more powerful than the manic panic box of bleach. But I didn’t leave any of the bleach on for as long as it was supposed to be? Like I just didn’t need it and I didn’t really care if certain parts were a tad uneven because I planned on dying it such a deep red that I just was like whatever. So I dyed it red and did some shadow roots to hide some of my fuck ups and holy shit it looks way better than what the salon lady did to my hair back in August. Honestly I was so surprised, but the reason I even got much of my results regardless of the fact that I committed the box bleach snafu is that I did a ton of online researching. My hair hasn’t fallen out, it isn’t burnt to a crisp, my curls are still very very present, and I took a lot of time doing it all because I wanted it to look good and I am such an amateur. Honestly, I’m super proud and if you want to see my hair check out my insta, I’ll be posting a pic tonight. (Nani2.5)
